
// This Hyperlambda code checks if an SMTP server is configured in the appSettings.json file. If the configuration is missing, it logs an error message and returns a boolean false, indicating failure in sending an email due to the lack of SMTP server configuration.
if
   eq
      get-value:x:@config.get
      .
   .lambda
      log.error:"Tried to send an email but couldn't since there is no SMTP server configured in your appSettings.json file"
      return-value:bool:false
